music

Interface ChordSequence

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Chord, ChordSequenceList, EmptyChordSequence, Measure, Repeat, Tuplet, Voice

    public interface ChordSequence
    The Interface ChordSequence represents any contiguous block of music from a single voice, including lyrics (because Chords contain their associated syllables) Immutable because it's an interface.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.util.List<Chord> getChords()
      Gets the chords associated with this ChordSequence.

    • Method Detail

      • getChords

        java.util.List<Chord> getChords()
        Gets the chords associated with this ChordSequence. Each Chord starts when the previous one ends, as encoded by Chord.duration (not to be confused with the duration of the individual notes within each Chord)
        Returns:
        a List of Chords that represents a contiguous block of music.
